<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12223&amp;p=138884#p138884"><![CDATA[
Counting video frames is a perfectly fine way to do turbo, seeing as the games themselves count video frames to see when to read the controller.<br /><br />Now to your question: Yes, you'll want it to do option one, a 50% <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Duty_cycle" class="postlink">duty cycle</a> (about as many 1's as 0's). You'll probably want to let the user choose one of several different fire rates: 11110000 (7.5 Hz), 111000 (10 Hz), 1100 (15 Hz), and 110 (20 Hz).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Jan 08, 2015 7:38 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
